# =============================================================
# Pressable .deployignore
# https://pressable.com/knowledgebase/deploy-from-github/
#
# IMPORTANT: Pressable's default sync DELETES any server files that
# are absent from the repo. This repo only tracks our custom theme,
# so without this file the first deploy would WIPE the site's other
# plugins (Elementor, WooCommerce, Ninja Forms, etc.) and themes.
#
# Strategy: exclude EVERYTHING from the deploy, then explicitly allow
# only our custom theme. Anything excluded here is left untouched on
# the server (deployed-as-is = false; preserved). Syntax mirrors
# .gitignore. This file must be committed BEFORE the first deploy.
# =============================================================

# Exclude everything (preserve on server, do not deploy/delete)...
/*

# ...but descend into wp-content
!/wp-content/
/wp-content/*

# ...and within wp-content, only themes
!/wp-content/themes/
/wp-content/themes/*

# ...and within themes, only our custom theme (fully managed by deploy)
!/wp-content/themes/dch-fse/

# Belt-and-suspenders: never deploy dev/build noise or VCS metadata,
# even if it somehow lands inside the theme.
.git/
.gitignore
.deployignore
**/node_modules/
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
